The paper deals with segmentation of robot movements, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses Gaussian mixture models (GMMs) for clustering, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of Kalman filters, which is a common technique in control systems and falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of position data, which is a common input in computer vision and falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes an autonomous segmentation method, which involves decision-making and falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
